    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0001">Downing</placeName> <choice>
                            <abbr>Nov<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                            </abbr>
                            <expan>November</expan>
                        </choice> 21. 1783.</dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I inclose  <rs type="art" ref="ardb.xml#ar0057">
                        <persName ref="pe0014">Moses</persName>'s Portrait by himself</rs>. 
                    he thinks himself highly flattered by <choice>
                        <abbr>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        </abbr>
                        <expan>your</expan>
                    </choice>
                    attention â€“ He also sends his bill as you desired. I see that <persName ref="pe0105">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Grose</persName>
                    advertises his work in <choice>
                        <abbr>oct<hi rend="superscript">vo</hi>
                        </abbr>
                        <expan>octavo</expan>
                    </choice>. 
                    so that I can b<del>e</del>uy what numbers I like without troubling you. But my 
                    <hi rend="underline">mind still turns on <rs type="art" ref="ardb.xml#ar0054">the Jail scene the frontespiece to <persName ref="pe0478">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Haily</persName>'s Poem to M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Howard</rs>
                    </hi>.
                    I write in great haste as we are going eighteen miles to dinner. I with <persName ref="pe0391">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Fitzmaurice</persName>
                    comptroller of a hunt <persName ref="pe0238">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Pennant</persName>
                    with <persName ref="pe0483">his Lady</persName>. This is quite reluctantly: but my regard for 
                    <persName ref="pe0391">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> <choice>
                            <abbr>Fitz..</abbr>
                            <expan>Fitzmaurice</expan>
                        </choice>
                    </persName>
                    whom<del>it</del> a party is trying to run down, urges me to make my appearance. I beg to have a little news especially about stocks 
                    &amp; taxes, &amp; shall rejoice to have a cordial from you this gloomy month.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Dear Sir
                        <lb/>most truely <choice>
                            <abbr>y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                            </abbr>
                            <expan>yours</expan>
                        </choice>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">
                            <choice>
                                <abbr>T</abbr>
                                <expan>Thomas</expan>
                            </choice> Pennant.</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="underline">
                            <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> White</persName> has a parcel</hi>
                        coming down, so will <hi rend="underline">receive</hi> any trifles you may have.</p>
                </postscript>
